message.content:
Explanation:

- The UserController::show method (App\Http\Controllers\UserController::show) is mapped to the GET /users/{user} web route (routes/web.php: Route::resource('users', ...)->only('show')).
- The controller method returns a Blade view (return view('users.show', [...])) and the method signature declares a View return type. Therefore the endpoint returns an HTML page (server-rendered HTML).
- The method uses route-model-binding for the User parameter. If the user is not found, Laravel will return a 404 Not Found response. The method does not perform any authorization checks, so 403 is not applicable here.
- Based on that, the relevant response status codes are:
  - 200: successful HTML view response (content is HTML).
  - 404: not found (HTML error page).
- In Swagger 2.0 response objects, I represent the content as a string schema (text/html). I avoid using $ref.

